messages.content:
I am creating an email to send to a client with their finished art commission. I have generated an image to place at the top of the email. I want you to create a fun email introduction that congratsulates them on completing the commission. Keep it as general as possible.

The introduction should only be a parapgraph in length and be raw text. Do not include a subject line or the "dear" section. It should simply the first paragraph of the email.

info.title: Final Feedback Form
info.description:
This is your final form (I promse). It is completely optional, but your feedback will help to improve our services and make the best art possible. 

It should only take a couple minutes - your opinion is greatly appreciated!

items.title: Ratings
items.description: Please rate each factor out of ten. You can give details at the end.

items.title: Customer Service
items.description: How did you feel our customer service was?

items.title: Quality of Art
items.description: Based strictly on the quality, how would you rate it?

items.title: Value for your Money
items.description: Do you feel the commission was worth the amount paid?

items.title: Would you choose us again?
items.description: How likely are you to order another piece?

items.title: More Detail (Optional)
items.description: Please give context on the previous ratings.

items.title: Section Complete
items.description: If you are willing to give more detailed feedback, you may continue.

items.title: Longer Questions
items.description:
Thanks for continuing!

This section is a bit longer, but each response gets read by management, so your feedback is extremly valuable.

items.title: What did you like about the commission process?
What did you not like? What could we change?
Are there any other types of commissions or listings that you wish we offered?
Is there anything else that you would like to share?

Hey {{3.`2`}}, ready for something exciting?

{{359.choices[].message.content}}

You can find the completed commission, as well as any previous versions (without those pesky watermarks) here:
{{32.shareLink}}

Additionally, there's a few links I would like to share:

Follow us on Instagram here:
{{42.`Instagram Link`}}

Check out our other Listings here:
{{44.`Etsy Link`}}

And as thanks for your trust and cooperation in the process, please help yourself to 25% off your next order:
{{45.`Coupon Code`}}

Lastly, if you would like to leave your artist a tip, you may do so at this link:
{{340.`6`}}

As always, a review on Etsy is greatly appreciated!

We look forward to creating something magical for you again!

Many Thanks as always,
Adam - Founder of Wattle Art Creations
